# Project: Interactive Shipping Calculator

# Stack: React, TypeScript, MUI, React Hook Form, Zod, Vite

## Code Style

- Always use TypeScript, never use `any`
- Always use named exports, never default exports for components
- Always use arrow functions for components
- File names must match component names exactly

## MUI Rules

- Never use inline styles or plain CSS
- Always use `sx` prop for one-off styles
- Always use `styled()` for reusable styled components
- Always pull values from theme (colors, spacing, typography)
- Never hardcode hex colors or pixel values

## React Hook Form Rules

- Always use `Controller` for MUI inputs
- Never use `watch()` on all fields - only watch specific fields
- Always validate with Zod schemas

## Folder Structure

- Features go in src/routes/<feature-name>/
- Each feature has: components/, hooks/, types/, schemas/
- Each feature must have an index.ts as its public API
- Never import from deep inside another feature
- Always import from feature's index.ts
- Shared components goes in src/components/
- Context goes in src/context/<context-name>
- App-level setup goes in src/app/

## Component Rules

- Every component must have a TypeScript interface for its props
- Every component file must have its own types at the top

## Naming Conventions

- Components: PascalCase (CourierCard.tsx)
- Hooks: camelCase with "use" prefix (useQuote.ts)
- Context: PascalCase with "Context" suffix (QuoteContext.tsx)
- Schemas: camelCase with "Schema" suffix (shippingSchema.ts)
- Types: PascalCase with "Type" suffix (CourierType.ts)
